> Now, deciding when to celebrate a festival is slightly tricky. For each
> festival/religious day, there is an epoch time. Usually it is the sunrise
> time. On whichever day the tithi of interest is active at sunrise, that day
> is celebrated as the religious day.
>
> However, there are some exceptions, as some religious observations are not
> made at sunrise, but at other times. For example, Satya Narayana pooja is
> supposed to be done at sunset. If one wants to do Satya Narayana pooja on a
